proxmox-storage-migrate (1.2.0-beta.1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * -s/-t are now required (from a flag or the config file below); they no
    longer default to empty and silently fail deep in storage.cfg lookup.
  * Add /etc/default/proxmox-storage-migrate: an optional config file
    setting new defaults for any flag. Command-line flags still override it.

 -- James Bolton <james@neojames.me>  Tue, 21 Jul 2026 17:40:00 +0100

proxmox-storage-migrate (1.1.0) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Running containers are now always stopped, migrated, and restarted
    (a container's volumes can't move live) instead of being left alone.
  * Initial Debian packaging: installs as /usr/bin/migrate-disks, with a
    man page.

 -- James Bolton <james@neojames.me>  Tue, 21 Jul 2026 17:00:00 +0100

proxmox-storage-migrate (1.0.0) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Initial release.

 -- James Bolton <james@neojames.me>  Tue, 21 Jul 2026 15:00:00 +0100
